I have a Google classroom for parents/guardians that will help you understand the Google platform we will be using with students. I encourage both adults and students to log on and check it out.

You need a gmail account and then follow these instructions for Google Classroom Access:
From a home desktop or laptop:
Locate the sign in button and sign into google (see above)
Locate the Google classroom app in the right hand corner (see above)
Enter your classroom code by clicking on the plus sign in the corner
Class code: okliorz

I highly recommend using a computer but google classroom does work on other devices. From an Android/iPhone or iPad, download the Google Classroom App/GMail app and follow the steps above.

post_text:
P-EBT Information:
If a family has an address change, activation question, reissue or want to know about status of P-EBT card they can call Human Service Customer Care number at 1-800-283-4465. This is a different number from what has been provided before which was a general EBT hotline. HSD has staff available to help and are trained to assist the P-EBT inquiries or changes. The PED only has minimal staff to assist questions at this time. Again, the district or schools and PED cannot change information or reissue cards as we do not have access to the HSD system.

Attention all Varsity and JV athletes, due to some delay in Covid testing with athletes and changes in the guidelines laid out by the NMAA, workouts will not begin until next Monday, June 22. There will still be a morning session from 8-9 and an evening session from 6-7. Please let your coaches know which session you will be attending. There is no access to locker rooms or water fountains so please come dressed in workout clothes and bring your own water bottle. Please wear a face mask or covering before and after workouts and practice social distancing.

Attention all Varsity and JV kids from all sports, we will be beginning workouts on Tues, 6/16. We will have an AM session and a PM session. To meet all guidelines as outlined by the NMAA we will be arranging Pods of 5 co-ed students to 1 coach. Workouts will be 1 hour long. You are asked to wear a mask or face covering to and from school and practice social distancing while you are here. Please bring your own water bottles facilities cannot be used. Coaches will be contacting you to determine at which time you are to report. Any questions or concerns please contact your coaches or Coach Mirabal @ (505)290-1426.

post_text: This week meal delivery will be at designated bus stops. Bus drivers will deliver Monday-Thursday of this week. The Magdalena Schools will be delivering meals on Tuesday April 14, 2020 because Monday is a holiday. Beginning April 14, 2020 We will be delivering once a week, on Mondays, with a full week of meals for the remainder of the school year. This new schedule will begin on April 14, 2020. Your bus driver should have contacted you regarding deliver times. We have made this change to reduce the amount of exposure to our staff, students, and parents.

text:
Per the guidance of Governor Michelle Lujan Grisham and recommendations from both the Departments of Health and Public Education, the 2020 NMAA State Basketball Championships will move forward without fans. To stream the game live online, please go to the NFHS Network (www.nfhsnetwork.com). A subscription fee of $10.99 will provide access to every state tournament game. MMSD will be sending home information today regarding our protocol for the COVID-19 virus.

post_text:
PAC (Parent Advisory Council) -October 16 at 11 AM in the Fine Arts is the next PAC meeting. All parents visiting for the parent luncheon will be invited.

October 18 - Pancake breakfast/pizza-posole lunch 10 am to 6 pm. The pancake breakfast will be free to those that visit a classroom (vouchers will be available). If you just want to eat some pancakes it will be $2/plate. Pizza $1/slice and Posole $3/bowl.

Need donations for the food ASAP and parents to sign up to work Oct 18 from 10am – 6pm.

Halloween Carnival Oct 31, 4-6pm – PAC will be doing the following booths: Painting booth, Slime and Costume Contest. We need parent volunteers for this event.

You can text Tamara Vinyard at 575-838-6142 or Leslie Clark at 575-838-3096 to get more information or sign up for a time.

PAC is a parent run organization and all parents are invited!

Last week Sheena Trujillo lost her home in a fire. Magdalena School employees are sponsoring the following events during the Girls District basketball game on Wednesday February 27th to help our co-worker and friend:

-Enchilada Dinner $6.00 a plate . The dinner will be served from 4:00 pm - 8:00 pm in the cafeteria.

-A Silent Auction will be conducted during the game.

-Our "new" steer mascot will also be wandering around the gym during games accepting donations. There will also be several donation jars set up around the gym area for you to contribute anonymously.
